data.content:
Three breaking changes affect your code. Here's each one and the fix:

---

### 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` ŌĆö now takes `Func<>`, not `Expression<Func<>>`

Your expression-tree construction **won't compile** anymore. Replace the entire block with:

```csharp
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

The new overload accepts a regular lambda, so conditional setters are just normal `if` statements.

---

### 2. Complex type column names ŌĆö now auto-uniquified

**Two sub-changes:**

**a) Same-named properties across sibling complex types** get a numeric suffix to avoid silent column sharing. If `ShippingAddress.Street` and `BillingAddress.Street` previously shared one column, EF 10 will generate `Street` and `Street1`. To preserve the old shared-column behavior (or control names), configure explicitly:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Customer>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress, p =>
        p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("ShippingAddress_Street"));
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress, p =>
        p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_Street"));
});
```

**b) Nested complex types now use full path in column names.** E.g. `Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City` was previously `BillingAddress_City`, now becomes `Payment_BillingAddress_City`. To keep old names:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Order>()
    .ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment)
    .ComplexProperty(p => p.BillingAddress)
    .Property(a => a.City)
    .HasColumnName("BillingAddress_City");
```

ŌÜĀ’ĖÅ If you have an existing database and add a migration, EF 10 will try to rename these columns. Pin column names explicitly to avoid a breaking migration.

---

### 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` ŌĆö new `logCommandText` parameter

All methods (`CommandReaderExecuting`, `CommandReaderExecuted`, etc.) now require an additional `string logCommandText` parameter. Update the signature:

```csharp
public class MyLogger : IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger
{
    public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
        IRelationalConnection connection,
        DbCommand command,
        DbContext context,
        Guid commandId,
        Guid connectionId,
        DateTimeOffset startTime,
        string logCommandText)   // ŌåÉ new parameter
    {
        // Use logCommandText for logging (constants may be redacted)
        // Use command.CommandText for actual SQL
    }
}
```

Apply the same addition to every method you implement on this interface.
